From Creamer Media in Johannesburg, this is the Real Economy Report. Sashnee Moodley: South African emerging domestic natural gas and helium producer Renergen earlier this month unveiled its Covid-19 vaccine transport solution, the Cryo-Vacc. Creamer Media journalist Simone Liedtke, who attended the unveiling event, tells us more. Simone Liedtke: Designed to keep Covid-19 vaccines ultra-cold during transportation for up to as much as 30 days, the Cryo-Vacc allows for vaccines to be transported over longer distances and to reach remote areas. Renergen CEO Stefano Marani talks to how the concept was born, while giving us a quick overview of the solution. Renergen CEO Stefano Marani: Simone Liedtke: However, the world is faced with infrastructural and logistical challenges. Marani further explains how the Cryo-Vacc addresses these issues. Renergen CEO Stefano Marani: Simone Liedtke: Market interest has also been on the uptake, with distribution and production to take place soon. Renergen CEO Stefano Marani:  Sashnee Moodley:  That’s Creamer Media’s Real Economy Report. Join us again next week for more news and insight into South Africa’s real economy. Don’t forget to listen to the audio version of our Engineering News daily email newsletter.